01:44:24.300 --> 01:44:26.300
Where was that Transylvania?

01:44:26.300 --> 01:44:28.300
Uh, actually...

01:44:28.300 --> 01:44:30.300
Seattle?

01:44:30.300 --> 01:44:32.300
More yams!

01:44:32.300 --> 01:44:41.240
What's going to change?

01:44:41.240 --> 01:44:43.240
Jed, you apologize right now.

01:44:43.240 --> 01:44:45.240
No, well, Ellen, it's all right.

01:44:45.240 --> 01:44:47.240
No harm done.

01:44:47.240 --> 01:44:49.240
You are excused from the table, young man.

01:44:49.240 --> 01:44:51.240
But Mom...

01:44:51.240 --> 01:45:17.820
Now, we're going out for coffee.

01:45:17.820 --> 01:45:19.820
Your dinner is in the Kelvinator.

01:45:19.820 --> 01:45:21.820
I'll deal with you when I get home.

01:45:21.820 --> 01:45:23.820
Hmm.

01:45:23.820 --> 01:45:36.250
Huey, I was wrong, man.

01:45:36.250 --> 01:45:38.250
I guess I must have been dreaming after all.

01:45:38.250 --> 01:45:40.250
That guy's not a werewolf.

01:45:40.250 --> 01:45:43.530
Yeah?

01:45:43.530 --> 01:45:45.530
Did you use pure silver?

01:45:45.530 --> 01:45:47.530
Yes. How about the moon?

01:45:47.530 --> 01:45:49.530
I did the test, all right.

01:45:49.530 --> 01:45:51.530
Okay, okay.

01:45:51.530 --> 01:45:53.530
So your mom's boyfriend isn't a werewolf.

01:45:53.530 --> 01:45:55.530
That's that. No, it's not.

01:45:55.530 --> 01:45:57.530
There's something going on over there.

01:45:57.530 --> 01:45:59.530
We've got to go back in that house.

01:45:59.530 --> 01:46:01.530
Oh, Jed, I'm taking a bath.

01:46:01.530 --> 01:46:05.320
Towel off.

01:46:05.320 --> 01:46:07.320
It looks pretty quiet.

01:46:07.320 --> 01:46:09.320
Maybe we should come back when somebody's home.

01:46:09.320 --> 01:46:12.700
Like noon?

01:46:12.700 --> 01:46:14.700
Come on, I know how we can get in.

01:46:14.700 --> 01:46:16.700
Wait, why do you keep saying we?

01:46:16.700 --> 01:46:18.700
Because we're partners, Huey.

01:46:18.700 --> 01:46:20.700
To the end.

01:46:20.700 --> 01:46:34.760
The end?

01:46:34.760 --> 01:46:36.760
You won't relax, nobody's home.

01:46:36.760 --> 01:47:00.900
I saw that having coffee with my mom.

01:47:00.900 --> 01:47:02.900
What's that?

01:47:02.900 --> 01:47:06.380
It's not really doing this.

01:47:06.380 --> 01:47:08.380
He's not really doing this.

01:47:08.380 --> 01:47:21.740
Turn around.

01:47:21.740 --> 01:47:23.740
Here, take this.

01:47:23.740 --> 01:47:32.940
Check this out.

01:47:32.940 --> 01:47:34.940
You thought you said it was full of him?

01:47:34.940 --> 01:47:36.940
He was. He must have hidden them.

01:47:36.940 --> 01:48:08.600
Maybe he got really hungry.

01:48:08.600 --> 01:48:12.100
That's proof.

01:48:12.100 --> 01:48:14.100
Uh, Jed?

01:48:14.100 --> 01:48:16.100
What does this guy look like?

01:48:16.100 --> 01:48:18.100
I don't know. Just like an average guy.

01:48:18.100 --> 01:48:20.100
Kind of tall?

01:48:20.100 --> 01:48:22.100
Kind of bald?

01:48:22.100 --> 01:48:24.100
Yeah, why? What difference does it make?

01:48:24.100 --> 01:48:29.370
Because I think he has a twin brother.

01:48:29.370 --> 01:48:31.370
He's gonna get a hold for very long.

01:48:31.370 --> 01:48:36.630
Thanks for the newsflash.

01:48:36.630 --> 01:49:06.250
Bad dog.

01:49:06.250 --> 01:49:57.820
I see you've met Gordon.

01:49:57.820 --> 01:50:22.790
My dad's in school.

01:50:22.790 --> 01:50:24.790
Gordon?

01:50:24.790 --> 01:50:32.140
My brother.

01:50:32.140 --> 01:50:36.060
Yeah, well, I got news for you, buddy.

01:50:36.060 --> 01:50:38.060
Your brother's got a problem.

01:50:38.060 --> 01:50:40.060
Yeah, I know.

01:50:40.060 --> 01:50:42.060
Lycanthropy is a terrible disease.

01:50:42.060 --> 01:50:44.060
Everybody tells me I should just

01:50:44.060 --> 01:50:46.060
put him out of his misery.

01:50:46.060 --> 01:50:48.060
But his family.

01:50:48.060 --> 01:50:50.060
It's all I got.

01:50:50.060 --> 01:50:52.060
Yeah, well, my mom's all I've got.

01:50:52.060 --> 01:50:54.060
And when she finds out about this, she's...

01:50:54.060 --> 01:50:56.060
Jed?

01:50:56.060 --> 01:51:02.950
I already know.

01:51:02.950 --> 01:51:06.260
You're not scared?

01:51:06.260 --> 01:51:08.260
I was at first, but I'm trying to understand, honey.

01:51:08.260 --> 01:51:11.540
I hope you will, too.

01:51:11.540 --> 01:51:15.660
Does he really eat...

01:51:15.660 --> 01:51:17.660
kids?

01:51:17.660 --> 01:51:21.260
Rumors.

01:51:21.260 --> 01:51:25.590
People can be so cruel.

01:51:25.590 --> 01:51:27.590
There's lots of different kinds of families, Jed.

01:51:27.590 --> 01:51:35.100
This is just one of them.

01:51:35.100 --> 01:51:37.100
Just gotta stop eating pets.

01:51:37.100 --> 01:51:40.470
It wasn't long before Jed's mom married

01:51:40.470 --> 01:51:42.470
the man from across the street.

01:51:42.470 --> 01:51:44.470
They all moved in together, like a family.

01:51:44.470 --> 01:51:48.140
Looking good, Mr. Anchors.

01:51:48.140 --> 01:51:50.140
Thank you, Mrs. Anchors.

01:51:50.140 --> 01:51:52.140
Two.

01:51:52.140 --> 01:51:54.140
Well done.

01:51:54.140 --> 01:51:56.140
And one.

01:51:56.140 --> 01:51:58.140
Me, too.

01:51:58.140 --> 01:52:00.140
Jed's mom was happy.

01:52:00.140 --> 01:52:02.140
The man was happy.

01:52:02.140 --> 01:52:04.140
And one very rare.

01:52:04.140 --> 01:52:13.300
Dinner time!

01:52:13.300 --> 01:52:15.300
Stay back! This one's out of the park!

01:52:15.300 --> 01:52:19.060
And as for Jed,

01:52:19.060 --> 01:52:21.060
he finally got his dog.

01:52:21.060 --> 01:52:31.830
The end.

01:52:31.830 --> 01:52:33.830
Our anniversary surprise.

01:52:33.830 --> 01:52:35.830
Surprise?

01:52:35.830 --> 01:52:37.830
Fire's nice and hot.

01:52:37.830 --> 01:52:39.830
What surprise?

01:52:39.830 --> 01:52:41.830
Special occasion.

01:52:41.830 --> 01:52:43.830
We planned it just for you.

01:52:43.830 --> 01:52:45.830
Roast.

01:52:45.830 --> 01:52:47.830
Frank.

01:52:47.830 --> 01:52:49.830
